The bodies of two people have been found amid the wreckage of a light aircraft after it crashed near a loch in western Scotland .
Police began combing woodland in Argyll following reports of a small plane losing contact with ground control .
At around 8 pm this evening officers discovered the remains of the two passengers thought to have been on board .
Lifeboats , helicopters and police were scrambled near Loch Etive , 30 miles from Oban .